 the U.S., Japan, or the U.K. and choose a stroke or match play game. Gameplay is from two point of views, starting with an overhead view allowing you to set up the shot and choose a club, then switching to a 3-D point of view. Hitting the ball uses the common power meter where tapping the button starts the meter, tap the button a second time to select the amount of power in the shot, then tap the button a third time to select the amount of slice or hook.","total_rating":61.01618897968407,"total_rating_count":19,"url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/nes-open-tournament-golf","videos":[{"id":35371,"video_id":"kceHby845NE"}],"websites":[{"id":772445,"url":"https://www.nintendo.com/games/detail/nes-open-tournament-golf-3ds/","type":{"id":24,"type":"Nintendo"}},{"id":315893,"url":"https://nintendo.fandom.com/wiki/NES_Open_Tournament_Golf","type":{"id":2,"type":"Community Wiki"}},{"id":515098,"url":"https://www.twitch.tv/directory/game/NES%20Open%20Tournament%20Golf","type":{"id":6,"type":"Twitch"}}]}